The paper deals with the problem of visual object tracking, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves designing measurement matrices and linear operators, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and matrix completion (cs.MM). The paper also uses a prior model for the images, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
